Hello! 👋
If you would like to contribute to this project by Asklepius Translation Services, you can simplify the process by following the steps below.

## 🧭 Prerequisites

- Having a GitHub account
- Basic knowledge of Markdown and translation processes
- Considering the sensitivity of health terms
- Experience working with CaféTran Espresso or similar CAT tools is an advantage

## 🚀 Contribution Types

- Adding new information about intraocular lens replacement surgery and/or refractive eye treatment, excimer laser eye treatment
- Grammar, spelling, or terminology corrections to existing content
- SEO-friendly title and meta description suggestions
- Optimizing file format (Markdown structure, title layout)

## 🔧 How to Contribute

1. Fork this repo

2. Create a new branch (such as `feature/turkish-fix`)
3. Make the necessary changes
4. Enter a descriptive commit message (`Fix mistranslation in Smart Lens intro`)
5. Submit a Pull Request (PR)

## 📋 PR Review Process

- Each PR will be reviewed for medical terminology and cultural appropriateness
- All contributions must be submitted with descriptive commits and PR descriptions
- Minor revisions may be requested if necessary

## 🧠 Language & Terminology Criteria

- Disease names, surgical procedures, and drug names are checked for consistency in Turkish, German, and English
- The same structure is maintained across all language versions: headings, paragraphs, and warnings
- Translation sensitivity is taken into account for cultural and ideological concepts such as Milli Görüş (National Vision)

